<br>
Fire: Transforms into a DoT that takes effect on the target, lowers targets AC. Dies in the process.<br>
<br>
Air: Dematerializes i.e. untargetable. Regenerates HP at a fast rate, but cannot reform and cannot be dismissed until a set time has passed.<br>
<br>
Earth: Becomes like stone! It takes 1/10th normal damage, yet deals no damage itself. Has a reset timer like air, moves at 20 percent base rate.<br>
<br>
Water: Encases your opponent, causing him to choke, DoT effect, possibly snare or slow. Dies in the process.<br>
<br>
This would give alot of diversity to our class as far our  <br>
soloing tactics go.. for instance, you might start off with water to slow your opponent, and follow it up with Fire, then with an earth pet.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uomegasyphon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>omegasyphon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 469<br> <font color=#333333>(10/10/02 1:17:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=75.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> comment</span><hr size=1> sounds good but um what is the point of the air one again? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzebanar01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zebanar01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 268<br> <font color=#333333>(10/10/02 4:56:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=75.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ah,</span><hr size=1> Air one would keep the pet from dying, although, I'd wager most of you probably wouldn't care about that..I tend to arm my pets to the teeth, and keep each pet as long as possible. One possibility, is that the air effect could act like the 'suspend pet' ability being talked about.. <br>
